      "tips": "Rest if needed. Light activity ok. Salt helps.",
      "metabolic": "Glycogen depleted. Liver ramping up ketone production (beta-hydroxybutyrate, acetoacetate, acetone). Brain still adapting - it prefers glucose but is learning to use ketones, causing 'brain fog'. Fat cells releasing fatty acids via lipolysis, producing waste products processed by liver. Insulin now very low, glucagon elevated. Growth hormone increases to preserve muscle. Sleep disruption common as norepinephrine rises. Uric acid may temporarily increase as kidneys adjust. Breath may smell fruity (acetone excretion).",
      "electrolytes": {
